Which of the following statements are valid ?

String[ ] sa = new String[3]{ "a", "b", "c"};
//You cannot specify the length of the array ( i.e. 3, here)
if you are using the initializer block while declaring the array.

String sa[ ] = { "a ", " b", "c"};

String sa = new String[ ]{"a", "b", "c"};
//here sa is not declared as array of strings but just as a String.

String sa[ ] = new String[ ]{"a", "b", "c"};

String sa[ ] = new String[ ] {"a" "b" "c"};
//There are no commas separating the strings.
